<subSubSection id="2BF24ACA1F68FF93FD5DFD72FC5C31C9" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="635719411F68FF93FD5DFD72FC5C31C9" blockId="35.[711,1175,659,718]" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">
Groupe de 
<taxonomicName id="A4E862C21F68FF93FCDCFD72FC5C31C9" authority="(Seem.) Mez" authorityName="Mez" baseAuthorityName="Seem." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Tapeinosperma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="scrobiculatum">
<emphasis id="519CC5531F68FF93FCDCFD72FB3D31A9" bold="true" box="[838,1175,659,686]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">Tapeinosperma scrobiculatum</emphasis>
(Seem.) Mez
</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2BF24ACA1F68FF93FD3FFD12FCF03640" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" type="description">
<paragraph id="635719411F68FF93FD3FFD12FC90300C" blockId="35.[675,1211,755,1351]" box="[677,826,755,781]" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">DESCRIPTION</paragraph>
<paragraph id="635719411F68FF93FD3FFCF3FC0F37E0" blockId="35.[675,1211,755,1351]" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">
Arbustes ou petits arbres ([1-]2-5[-8] m), parfois peu ramifiés. Limbes de dimensions moyennes à grandes. Inflorescences en panicule terminale, généralement sur des rameaux normaux, occasionnellement, au moins pour certaines espèces (
<taxonomicName id="A4E862C21F68FF93FD34FC50FCC030CC" authority="Mez" authorityName="Mez" box="[686,874,945,971]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Tapeinosperma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="minutum">
<emphasis id="519CC5531F68FF93FD34FC50FC9A30CD" box="[686,816,945,970]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">T. minutum</emphasis>
Mez
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="A4E862C21F68FF93FCEFFC50FBF430CC" authority="Mez" authorityName="Mez" box="[885,1118,944,971]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Tapeinosperma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="oblongifolium">
<emphasis id="519CC5531F68FF93FCEFFC50FB8C30CD" box="[885,1062,944,970]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">T. oblongifolium</emphasis>
Mez
</taxonomicName>
) sur des rameaux latéraux spéciaux, 2-3 fois ramifiées, à axes finement scrobiculés-verruqueux. Fleurs pédicellées (pédicelles filiformes longs de 
<quantity id="A410B4A41F68FF93FBD6FBEEFB06372D" box="[1100,1196,1039,1066]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="2.0">2-5 mm</quantity>
), relativement petites pour le genre (
<quantity id="A410B4A41F68FF93FBA5FBCEFB1D374D" box="[1087,1207,1071,1098]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.5">1,5-3 mm</quantity>
, 
<quantity id="A410B4A41F68FF93FD3FFBAEFD56376E" box="[677,764,1103,1129]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" unit="mm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3-4 mm</quantity>
cependant dans 
<taxonomicName id="A4E862C21F68FF93FC2BFBB1FB1F376E" authority="M.Schmid" authorityName="M. Schmid" authorityYear="2012" box="[945,1205,1103,1129]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Primulaceae" genus="Tapeinosperma" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ericales" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="amieuense" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="519CC5531F68FF93FC2BFBB1FB9D376E" box="[945,1079,1104,1129]" italics="true" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">T. amieuense</emphasis>
M.Schmid
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel id="4AAF78281F68FF93FD3FFB8EFCAB378E" box="[677,769,1135,1161]" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), de teinte blanchâtre à rose lilas sur le vivant. Styles filiformes, longs de 
<quantity id="A410B4A41F68FF93FB94FB6FFBD537AE" box="[1038,1151,1166,1193]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.25" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="35" pageNumber="314" unit="mm" value="2.25" valueMax="3.0" valueMin="1.5">1,5-3 mm</quantity>
. Stigmates ponctiformes. Fruits globuleux de (3-)4- 6(-8) mm de diamètre.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="635719411F68FF93FD21FB0CFCF03640" blockId="35.[675,1211,755,1351]" pageId="35" pageNumber="314">Espèces croissant en forêt, principalement – pour plusieurs d’entre elles exclusivement – sur terrains siliceux.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
